The paper discusses the use of Moving Target Defense systems for web applications, which is a topic related to cyber security (cs.CR). The proposed approach involves modeling the ecosystem as a Bayesian Stackelberg game, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the need for the administrator to secure the web application, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE). The use of different configurations to mask vulnerabilities is a technique related to system integration (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the design of switching strategies, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
